parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting and corrosion of the frame can lead to structural failure, compromising the vehicle's safety and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rust holes in the frame
corrosion near the control arm
rear trailing arm mount detachment
loss of control while driving
uneven vehicle movement
and a feeling of the vehicle "floating" or "swaying" while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. The failure of the frame can also result in the separation of critical components, such as the rear axle, leading to loss of control and potential rollover.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit unusual handling or swaying
particularly when driving over bumps or rough roads. The rear end of the vehicle may wobble or jerk
making it difficult to control. In some cases
the vehicle may experience a sudden loss of control
leading to accidents or near-misses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension and axle can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. The failure of these components can also result in the separation of critical components, such as the rear axle, leading to loss of control and potential rollover.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit unusual handling or swaying
particularly when driving over bumps or rough roads. The rear end of the vehicle may wobble or jerk
making it difficult to control. In some cases
the vehicle may experience a sudden loss of control
leading to accidents or near-misses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge readings can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel, leading to accidents, strandings, and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: The fuel gauge shows incorrect readings
such as full when the tank is empty
or empty when there are still several gallons of fuel left. The gauge may also fluctuate erratically
making it difficult to determine the actual fuel level.
